	\section{Introduction to LaTeX}
	LaTeX is a high-quality typesetting system commonly used for academic and scientific documents. It provides professional formatting, mathematical typesetting, and powerful document structuring. Unlike WYSIWYG editors, LaTeX allows users to focus on content while ensuring consistent formatting.
	
	\section{Lists in LaTeX}
	\subsection{Bulleted List}
	\begin{itemize}
		\item LaTeX is powerful
		\item Used for research papers
		\item Supports complex document structures
	\end{itemize}
	
	\subsection{Numbered List}
	\begin{enumerate}
		\item Introduction to LaTeX
		\item Writing structured documents
		\item Advanced formatting features
	\end{enumerate}
	
	\subsection{Definition List}
	\begin{description}
		\item[LaTeX] A document preparation system.
		\item[TeX] A typesetting language.
		\item[Overleaf] An online LaTeX editor.
	\end{description}
	
